[{"Id": 1002998, "EnglishTitle": null, "GujaratiTitle": null, "RUrduTitle": null, "UrduTitle": null, "Sequence": null, "EnglishDescription": "The following is quoted from the book of Zad al-Ma’ad by Allamah Majlisi. It is highly advisable not to neglect mentioning the dead, because they are now too short to do any righteous or charitable deed. They therefore hope that their sons, relatives, and brethren in-faith will do charitable acts on behalf of them or pray for them, especially at the night-time prayers. An individual is required to pray for his parents in the post-prayer supplicatory utterances and at visiting the holy shrines and to do charitable and righteous acts on behalf of them.", "GujaratiDescription": null, "RUrduDescription": "Allama Majlisi ne Zaad al-Maad mein farmaya hai keh marne waalo’n ko faraamosh nahi karna chaahiye kyu-keh woh khud to amaal-e-khair anjaam nahi de paate woh sirf apni aulaad, rishte-daaro’n aur momin bhaiyyo’n se aas lagaaye huwe hai aur unki nekiyo’n ke liye chashm barah hai, pas khaas taur par Namaz-e-Shab, waajib namazo’n ke baad aur maqaamaate muqaddasa ki ziyarat ke mauqe par un ke liye dua karna chahiye aur waaledain ke liye dusro’n se kuchh ziyadah dua karna chahiye neez unke liye amaal-e-khair baja laane chahiye.", "UrduDescription": "انشاء اللہ ترجمہ جلد آرہا ہے", "English": null, "Gujarati": null, "RGujarati": null, "RUrdu": null, "Urdu": null, "RArabic": null, "ArabicText1": null, "ArabicGreenSign1": null, "ArabicRedSign1": null, "ArabicBlueSign1": null, "ArabicText2": null, "ArabicGreenSign2": null, "ArabicRedSign2": null, "ArabicBlueSign2": null, "ArabicText3": null, "ArabicGreenSign3": null, "ArabicRedSign3": null, "ArabicBlueSign3": null, "ArabicText4": null, "ArabicGreenSign4": null, "ArabicRedSign4": null, "ArabicBlueSign4": null, "ArabicText5": null, "ArabicGreenSign5": null, "ArabicRedSign5": null, "ArabicBlueSign5": null, "ArabicText6": null, "ArabicGreenSign6": null, "ArabicRedSign6": null, "ArabicBlueSign6": null, "ArabicText7": null, "ArabicGreenSign7": null, "ArabicRedSign7": null, "ArabicBlueSign7": null, "ArabicText8": null, "ArabicGreenSign8": null, "ArabicRedSign8": null, "ArabicBlueSign8": null, "ArabicText9": null, "ArabicGreenSign9": null, "ArabicRedSign9": null, "ArabicBlueSign9": null, "ArabicText10": null, "ArabicGreenSign10": null, "ArabicRedSign10": null, "ArabicBlueSign10": null, "ArabicText11": null, "ArabicGreenSign11": null, "ArabicRedSign11": null, "ArabicBlueSign11": null, "ArabicText12": null, "ArabicGreenSign12": null, "ArabicRedSign12": null, "ArabicBlueSign12": null, "ArabicText13": null, "ArabicGreenSign13": null, "ArabicRedSign13": null, "ArabicBlueSign13": null, "ArabicText14": null, "ArabicGreenSign14": null, "ArabicRedSign14": null, "ArabicBlueSign14": null, "ArabicText15": null, "ArabicGreenSign15": null, "ArabicRedSign15": null, "ArabicBlueSign15": null, "ArabicText16": null, "ArabicGreenSign16": null, "ArabicRedSign16": null, "ArabicBlueSign16": null, "ArabicText17": null, "ArabicGreenSign17": null, "ArabicRedSign17": null, "ArabicBlueSign17": null, "ArabicText18": null, "ArabicGreenSign18": null, "ArabicRedSign18": null, "ArabicBlueSign18": null, "ArabicText19": null, "ArabicGreenSign19": null, "ArabicRedSign19": null, "ArabicBlueSign19": null, "ArabicText20": null, "ArabicGreenSign20": null, "ArabicRedSign20": null, "ArabicBlueSign20": null, "EnglishImage": null, "GujaratiImage": null, "RUrduImage": null, "UrduImage": null, "IsRed": 0, "MinimizeDescriptionLine": 1, "IsPrintable": 0}, {"Id": 1002999, "EnglishTitle": null, "GujaratiTitle": null, "RUrduTitle": null, "UrduTitle": null, "Sequence": null, "EnglishDescription": "A tradition holds that an individual who may be impious to his parents can be recorded as pious to them after their death when he does charitable and righteous acts on behalf of them; while an individual who is pious to his parents in their lifetimes may be decided as impious to them after their death, because he disregards doing any charitable or righteous act on behalf of them. The best charitable favor that is done to one’s parents or relatives is to settle their debts and to release them from any liability towards Almighty Allah or towards other people. Hence, one may do his best to go on the ritual pilgrimage (Hajj) on behalf of the dead or to make up for the obligatory acts of worship that they missed to do, either voluntarily or by employing someone to do that for a certain wage.", "GujaratiDescription": null, "RUrduDescription": "Ek aur riwaayat mein aaya hai keh bohot se aulaade’n aisi hoti hai keh waaledain ki maujoodgi mein unki na-farmaan hoti hai lekin unke marne ke baad unke liye amaale khair baja laane ke baais farma’n bardaar ban jaati hai aur usi tarah bohot se aulaade’n aisi hai jo waaledain ki zindagi mein unki farmaan-bardaar hoti hai lekin unke marne ke baad unke liye amaale khair baja na laane ya kam baja laane se na-farmaan ho jaati hai. Apne marhoom waaledain aur rishte-daaro’n ke liye sab se behtar aur umdah neki yeh hai keh unke waajib qarze adaa kiye jaaye aur unhe huqooqullah aur huqooqul ebaad se chhut-kaara dilaaya jaaye aur un par Hajj ya dusri ibaadat ki jo adaayegi waajib thi who khud ya ujrat de kar adaa karaayi jaaye.", "UrduDescription": null, "English": null, "Gujarati": null, "RGujarati": null, "RUrdu": null, "Urdu": null, "RArabic": null, "ArabicText1": null, "ArabicGreenSign1": null, "ArabicRedSign1": null, "ArabicBlueSign1": null, "ArabicText2": null, "ArabicGreenSign2": null, "ArabicRedSign2": null, "ArabicBlueSign2": null, "ArabicText3": null, "ArabicGreenSign3": null, "ArabicRedSign3": null, "ArabicBlueSign3": null, "ArabicText4": null, "ArabicGreenSign4": null, "ArabicRedSign4": null, "ArabicBlueSign4": null, "ArabicText5": null, "ArabicGreenSign5": null, "ArabicRedSign5": null, "ArabicBlueSign5": null, "ArabicText6": null, "ArabicGreenSign6": null, "ArabicRedSign6": null, "ArabicBlueSign6": null, "ArabicText7": null, "ArabicGreenSig